1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,131
Cecil now realized that how old we are is not important.

2
00:00:04,321 --> 00:00:09,250
It's one's attitude toward age that makes it a blessing or a barricade.

3
00:00:09,921 --> 00:00:17,010
Curing yourself of age excusitis often opens doors to opportunities that you thought were locked tight.

4
00:00:17,441 --> 00:00:23,411
A relative of mine spent years doing many different things, selling, operating his own business,

5
00:00:23,521 --> 00:00:28,530
working in a bank, but he never quite found what he really wanted to do most.

6
00:00:28,801 --> 00:00:34,770
Finally, he concluded that the one thing he wanted more than anything else was to be a minister.

7
00:00:34,961 --> 00:00:38,290
But when he thought about it, he found he was too old.

8
00:00:38,401 --> 00:00:43,490
After all, he was forty-five, had three young children, and little money.

9
00:00:44,081 --> 00:00:50,290
But fortunately, he mustered all of his strength and told himself, Forty-five or not,

10
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,371
I'm going to be a minister.

11
00:00:53,121 --> 00:01:00,530
With tons of faith but little else, he enrolled in a five-year ministerial training program in Wisconsin.

12
00:01:00,801 --> 00:01:07,331
Five years later, he was ordained as a minister and settled down with a fine congregation in Illinois.

13
00:01:07,921 --> 00:01:08,611
Old?

14
00:01:08,801 --> 00:01:09,891
Of course not.

15
00:01:10,161 --> 00:01:13,651
He still has twenty years of productive life ahead of him.

16
00:01:13,841 --> 00:01:17,331
I talked with this man not long ago, and he said to me,

17
00:01:17,761 --> 00:01:22,691
You know, if I had not made that great decision when I was forty-five,

18
00:01:22,801 --> 00:01:26,371
I would have spent the rest of my life growing old and bitter.

19
00:01:26,641 --> 00:01:30,851
Now I feel every bit as young as I did twenty-five years ago.

20
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:33,731
And he almost looked it, too.

21
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:41,251
When you lick age-excusitis, the natural result is to gain the optimism of youth and feel of youth.

22
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:48,530
When you beat down your fears of age limitations, you add years to your life, as well as success.

23
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:56,771
A former university colleague of mine provides an interesting angle on how age-excusitis was defeated.

24
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:00,691
Bill was graduated from Harvard in the 1920s.

25
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:06,771
After 24 years in the stock brokerage business, during which time he made a modest fortune,

26
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:10,291
Bill decided he wanted to become a college professor.

27
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:16,371
Bill's friends warned him that he would overtax himself in the rugged learning program ahead.

28
00:02:16,641 --> 00:02:23,811
But Bill was determined to reach his goal and enrolled in the University of Illinois at the age of 51.

29
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:27,010
At fifty-five, he had earned his degree.

30
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:32,610
Today, Bill is chairman of the Department of Economics at a fine liberal arts college.

31
00:02:32,641 --> 00:02:33,971
He's happy, too.

32
00:02:34,161 --> 00:02:39,331
He smiles when he says, I've got almost a third of my good years left.

33
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,530
Old age is a failure disease.

34
00:02:42,721 --> 00:02:45,891
Defeat it by refusing to let it hold you back.

